'''Marcus Holmgren Pedersen''' (born 16 July 2000) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for Italian {{Italian football updater|Torino}} club [[Torino FC|Torino]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].<ref name="sw">{{Soccerway|marcus-holmgren-pedersen/549159|accessdate=28 November 2018}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early life===
Hailing from [[Hammerfest (town)|Hammerfest]], Pedersen started playing youth football in [[HIF/Stein]]. In 2016 he moved to [[Tromsø (city)|Tromsø]] to attend the [[Norwegian School of Elite Sport]] there, and transferred to the youth section of Tromsø IL.<ref>{{cite news|title=Her er de beste av de eldste|work=Nordlys|date=30 December 2017|author=Nyvoll, David|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Tromsø===
Pedersen got his debut for Tromsø when he came in as an 86th-minute substitute in a [[Norwegian Football Cup|Norwegian Cup]] first round tie against Skjervøy on 18 April 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=919782&tournamentId=110&seasonId=340&useFullUrl=false |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419235242/http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=919782&tournamentId=110&seasonId=340&useFullUrl=false |url-status=dead |archive-date=19 April 2018 |title=Skjervøy 1-3 Tromsø |website=altomfotball.no |publisher=[[TV2 (Norway)|TV2]] |accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>  He got his league debut in a 1–0 loss against [[Odds BK|Odd]] on 28 October 2018, and became the first player from [[Hammerfest (town)|Hammerfest]] to play in the top division of Norwegian football.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aftenposten.no/sport/fotball/i/OpyMOl/her-er-hammerfests-foerste-eliteseriespiller-en-fantastisk-foelelse |title=Her er Hammerfests første eliteseriespiller: – En fantastisk følelse |work=[[ITromsø]] |publisher=[[Aftenposten]] |first=Tobias |last=Eilertsen |date=29 October 2019|accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> 
On 5 May 2019, he received a red card for a professional foul and was sent off in the 88th minute of the game against [[Kristiansund BK|Kristiansund]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aftenposten.no/sport/fotball/i/GGO3yx/saa-lenge-maa-til-klare-seg-uten-holmgren-pedersen |title=Så lenge må TIL klare seg uten Holmgren Pedersen |work=[[ITromsø]] |publisher=[[Aftenposten]] |first=Mats |last=Rydland |date=10 May 2019 |accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Molde===
On 11 February 2020, Pedersen signed a three-year contract with [[Molde FK|Molde]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/holmgren-pedersen-klar-for-mfk |title=Holmgren Pedersen klar for MFK! |website=moldefk.no |publisher=[[Molde FK]] |accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>

===Feyenoord===
On 22 June 2021, Molde confirmed that they had sold Pedersen to [[Feyenoord]],<ref>{{cite web |title=HOLMGREN PEDERSEN KLAR FOR FEYENOORD! |url=https://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/holmgren-pedersen-klar-for-feyenoord |website=moldefk.no/ |publisher=Molde FK |access-date=22 June 2021 |language=Norwegian |date=22 June 2021}}</ref> with the Dutch club confirming the arrival of the defender on a five-year contract the same day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Feyenoord vindt in Holmgren Pedersen nieuwe rechtsback |url=https://www.feyenoord.nl/nieuws/nieuwsoverzicht/feyenoord-vindt-in-holmgren-pedersen-nieuwe-rechtsback---220621 |website=feyenoord.nl |publisher=Feyenoord |access-date=22 June 2021 |language=Dutch |date=22 June 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 18 February 2023, scoring the second goal in the 90th minute in a 2–1 win over [[AZ Alkmaar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/kuip-in-extase-marcus-pedersen-schiet-feyenoord-in-slotminuut-langs-az~a573a4bf/ |title=Kuip in extase: Marcus Pedersen schiet Feyenoord in slotminuut langs AZ |trans-title=Kuip in rapture: Marcus Pedersen shoots Feyenoord past AZ in the final minute |language=Dutch |date=18 February 2023 |access-date=19 February 2023}}</ref>

====Sassuolo (loan)====
On 22 August 2023, Pedersen joined Italian club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on loan for the remainder of the season, with an option to buy.<ref name="Pedersen">{{cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/6277546/feyenoord-laat-pedersen-op-huurbasis-naar-sassuolo-vertrekken.html |title=Feyenoord laat Pedersen op huurbasis naar Sassuolo vertrekken |trans-title=Feyenoord lets go to Sassuolo on loan |language=Dutch |date=22 August 2023 |access-date=22 August 2023}}</ref>

====Torino (loan)====
On 22 August 2024, Pedersen returned to Italy and signed with [[Torino FC|Torino]] on loan, with an option to buy and a conditional obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Torino|url=https://www.torinofc.it/news/22/08/2024/pedersen-al-toro_29310|title=Pedersen al Toro|trans-title=Pedersen to Toro|date=22 August 2024|access-date=22 August 2024|language=it}}</ref>

==International career==
Marcus Holmgren Pedersen played nine games and scored one goal for  [[Norway national under-19 football team|Norway under-19]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotball.no/fotballdata/person/profil/?p=n&fiksId=3471242 |title=Marcus Holmgren Pedersen |website=fotball.no |publisher=[[Norwegian Football Federation]] |accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> On 27 February 2019, he scored in his debut game against [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark]] which Norway lost 2–1. Pedersen was a member of Norway's squad in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2019 European Under-19 Championship]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotball.no/landslag/norge-gutter-19/2019/her-er-g19-landslagets-em-tropp/ |title=G19: Her er Norges EM-tropp |website=fotball.no |publisher=[[Norwegian Football Federation]] |date= 24 June 2019 |accessdate=11 February 2020 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> and appeared in all three matches in the group stage.

He made his debut for the [[Norway national football team]] on 1 September 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group G|World Cup qualifier]] against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], a 1–1 home draw. He started the game and was substituted after an hour of play.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/uefa/match-center/400155708|title=Norway v Netherlands game report|date=1 September 2021}}</ref>

